{"action": "input", "code": "def find_blue_objects(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and returns a list of tuples, where each tuple represents the center of a 3x3 grid\n    with black center and blue surrounding pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples, where each tuple represents the center of a 3x3 grid with black center and blue surrounding pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_objects = []\n    for i in range(1, input_grid.shape[0] - 1):\n        for j in range(1, input_grid.shape[1] - 1):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == black and np.all(input_grid[i - 1:i + 2, j - 1:j + 2] == blue):\n                blue_objects.append((i, j))\n    return blue_objects\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blue_object = find_blue_objects(input_grid)\n    input_grid = replace_blue_with_red_cross(input_grid, blue_object)\n    return input_grid\ndef replace_blue_with_red_cross(input_grid: np.ndarray, blue_objects: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and a list of tuples representing the center of a 3x3 grid with black center and\n    blue surrounding pixels. It replaces the blue pixels with red pixels in the 3x3 grid and puts a red cross-shaped\n    object at the center of the 3x3 grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid\n    blue_objects: A list of tuples, where each tuple represents the center of a 3x3 grid with black center and blue\n                  surrounding pixels.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    for obj in blue_objects:\n        i, j = obj\n        input_grid[i - 1:i + 2, j - 1:j + 2] = red\n        input_grid[i, j] = black\n        input_grid[i - 1:i + 2, j] = red\n        input_grid[i, j - 1:j + 2] = red\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(inpu