{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_blue_objects(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds all 3x3 grids in the input grid where all pixels are blue except the center pixel.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the blue objects found in the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_objects = []\n    for i in range(1, input_grid.shape[0] - 1):\n        for j in range(1, input_grid.shape[1] - 1):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == blue and input_grid[i - 1][j - 1] == blue and (input_grid[i - 1][j] == blue) and (input_grid[i - 1][j + 1] == blue) and (input_grid[i][j - 1] == blue) and (input_grid[i][j + 1] == blue) and (input_grid[i + 1][j - 1] == blue) and (input_grid[i + 1][j] == blue) and (input_grid[i + 1][j + 1] == blue):\n                blue_objects.append(input_grid[i - 1:i + 2, j - 1:j + 2])\n    return np.array(blue_objects)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blue_object = find_blue_objects(input_grid)\n    input_grid = replace_blue_red_across(input_grid, blue_object)\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blue_object = `find the 3*3 grids with pixels blue except the center in the input_grid`(input_grid)\n    input_grid = replace_blue_red_across(input_grid, blue_object)\n    return input_grid", "gpt_code": "def find_blue_objects(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds all 3x3 grids in the input grid where all pixels are blue except the center pixel.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the blue objects found in the input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_objects = []\n    for i in range(1, input_grid.shape[0] - 1):\n        for j in range(1, input_grid.shape[1] - 1):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == blue and input_grid[i - 1][j - 1] == blue and (input_grid[i - 1][j] == blue) and (input_grid[i