{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_blue_objects(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds all 3x3 grids in the input grid where all pixels except the center one are blue.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the coordinates of the top-left pixel of each blue object found.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_objects = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0] - 2):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1] - 2):\n            if np.all(input_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3] == blue):\n                blue_objects.append((i + 1, j + 1))\n    return blue_objects\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blue_object = find_blue_objects(input_grid)\n    input_grid = replace_blue_with_red_cross(input_grid, blue_object)\n    return input_grid\ndef replace_blue_with_red_cross(input_grid: np.ndarray, blue_objects: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replaces all blue pixels around the blue objects with black pixels and puts a 3x3 red cross-shaped object at their places.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    blue_objects: A list of tuples representing the coordinates of the top-left pixel of each blue object found.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    for obj in blue_objects:\n        i, j = obj\n        input_grid[i - 1:i + 2, j - 1:j + 2] = red\n        input_grid[i, j] = black\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    blue_object = `find the 3*3 grids with pixels blue except the center in the input_grid`(input_grid)\n    input_grid = `make the blue pixels around the blue_object black ,and put 3*3 red cross-shaped object at their places`(input_grid, blue_object)\n    return input_grid", "gpt_code": "def find_blue_objects(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds all 3x3 grids in the input grid where all pixels except the center one are blue.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of tuples representing the coordinates of the top-left pixel of each blue object found.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_objects = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0] - 2):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1] - 2):\n            if np.all(input_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3] == blue):\n                blue_objects.append((i + 1, j + 1))\n    return blue_objects\ndef replace_blue_with_red_cross(input_grid: np.ndarray, blue_objects: List[Tuple[int, int]]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replaces all blue pixels around the blue objects with black pixels and puts a 3x3 red cross-shaped object at their places.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    blue_objects: A list of tuples representing the coordinates of the top-left pixel of each blue object found.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    for obj in blue_objects:\n        i, j = obj\n        input_grid[i - 1:i + 2, j - 1:j + 2] = red\n        input_grid[i, j] = black\n    return input_grid", "holes": {"find_blue_objects": "find the 3*3 grids with pixels blue except the center in the input_grid", "replace_blue_with_red_cross": "make the blue pixels around the blue_object black ,and put 3*3 red cross-shaped object at their places"}}
